claim.claim-text:
1. A fuel cell system, comprising: 
a fuel cell having a cathode gas inlet, and an anode gas inlet; 
a sensor configured to monitor a parameter associated with performance of the fuel cell during operation; 
a first apparatus configured to communicate cathode gas to the cathode gas inlet during operation of the fuel cell; 
a second apparatus configured to communicate an anode gas to the anode gas inlet during operation; and 
a controller in communication with the sensor and the first and second apparatus so that, when the parameter reaches a predetermined value, the controller sends a signal to the first apparatus that reduces the flow rate of the cathode gas to the cathode gas manifold.
